# Gateway architecture (`apps/gateway`)

Organize by **domain capability**, not horizontal layers (`plumbing/`, `core/`, `features/`). Each folder owns one concern: one or two `@injectable()` services, helpers, and a colocated `tests/` directory.

Do **not** create empty domain folders ahead of need. Add a folder when a story implements that capability.

## Domain map (Linear stories ‚Üí folders)

| Story | Folder | Owns |
|-------|--------|------|
| 1 ‚Äî Config | `config/` | Boot-time load, env resolution, zod validation, `ToriiConfigService` |
| 2 ‚Äî Connections | `backends/` | Backend registry, connection state, MCP client connector |
| 3 ‚Äî Tool catalog | `catalog/` | Fan-out `tools/list`, namespacing (`server.tool`) |
| 4a‚Äìc ‚Äî Auth | `credentials/` | OBO / `service_key` / `none` credential resolvers |
| 5 ‚Äî Dispatch | `dispatch/` | Route `tools/call` to the correct backend |
| 6 ‚Äî Policy | `policy/` | List-level and call-level policy enforcement |
| 7 ‚Äî Tracing | `trace/` | Structured `CallTrace` emission |
| ‚Äî MCP surface | `mcp/` | Inbound gateway MCP server (Fastify + SDK); delegates to domain services |

`config/` mixes boot infrastructure (`utils/loader.ts`, `utils/schema.ts`, `utils/env-resolver.ts`) with the runtime read-only service (`torii-config.service.ts`). Keep parsing/validation out of services.

## Folder conventions

```
src/
  config/           # exists ‚Äî boot + ToriiConfigService
  backends/         # Story 2
  catalog/          # Story 3
  credentials/      # Story 4
  dispatch/         # Story 5
  policy/           # Story 6
  trace/            # Story 7
  mcp/              # inbound protocol handlers
  container.ts      # tsyringe registrations
  index.ts          # process entry / boot sequence
```

Within each domain folder:

```
module/
  *.service.ts       # @injectable() orchestration (one or two per module)
  types/             # interfaces and type aliases
  utils/             # pure helpers, parsers, validators
  tests/             # colocated tests
```

- **Service** ‚Äî `*.service.ts` at the module root (e.g. `connection-manager.service.ts`, `tool-catalog.service.ts`)
- **Types** ‚Äî `types/` (e.g. `types/backend-connection.ts`, `types/catalog-tool.ts`)
- **Utils** ‚Äî `utils/` for stateless helpers (e.g. `utils/namespacing.ts`, `utils/loader.ts`)
- **Infra adapters** ‚Äî thin SDK/HTTP wrappers as `*.service.ts` at module root when injectable (e.g. `mcp-client-connector.service.ts`)
- **Tests** ‚Äî `tests/*.test.ts` beside the code they cover

`config/` keeps boot infrastructure in `utils/` (`loader.ts`, `schema.ts`, `env-resolver.ts`) alongside `torii-config.service.ts`.

### `credentials/` layout

Strategy implementations live under `resolvers/`; the domain facade (`credential-resolver.service.ts`) and shared contracts (`types/`, `utils/`, oauth token repo) stay at the domain root.

```
credentials/
  credential-resolver.service.ts   # strategy dispatch facade
  resolvers/                       # none | service_key | oauth_obo
    tests/                         # unit tests for resolver behavior
  tests/
    test-helpers.ts
    integration/                   # wiring tests (backends, catalog, live MCP)
```

Unit tests belong under `resolvers/tests/`; cross-domain integration tests belong under `tests/integration/`. Do not nest full per-strategy modules unless a strategy grows its own adapters, types, and helpers.

## `mcp/` vs domain services

`mcp/` is the **front door** only: wire Fastify routes and MCP SDK handlers. It must **delegate** to domain services ‚Äî no fan-out, policy, or credential logic here.

```text
Agent ‚Üí mcp/ (tools/list, tools/call)
          ‚Üí catalog/ | dispatch/
               ‚Üí credentials/ | policy/ | backends/
```

## DI (tsyringe, not Nest)

- Register services in `container.ts`
- Use `@injectable()` on services; constructor injection for dependencies
- No `@Module()` decorators ‚Äî folder boundaries replace Nest modules

## Avoid

- Horizontal layer dirs: `plumbing/`, `core/`, `features/`, `infra/`, `domain/`
- Folders named by story number (`story-3/`)
- Empty placeholder directories for future stories
- Business logic in `index.ts` or `mcp/` handlers
